---
import {getCollection} from "astro:content"; import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro"; import ArchiveNotice from "../../components/ArchiveNotice.astro";
const all=(await getCollection("writing",({data})=>!data.draft&&data.slug!=="legacy-archive")).sort((a,b)=>(b.data.date?.valueOf()||0)-(a.data.date?.valueOf()||0));
---
<BaseLayout title="Writing archive" description="Chronological archive and migration status for legacy writing." type="Writing"><header class="page-head"><div class="container"><p class="eyebrow">Archive</p><h1>Chronology, kept in context.</h1><p class="lead">Curated notes appear below; the full pre-rebuild source remains on the legacy branch while editorial review continues.</p></div></header><div class="container content-shell"><aside><ArchiveNotice/></aside><article class="prose"><h2>Curated chronology</h2><ol>{all.map(item=><li><a href={`/writing/${item.data.slug}/`}>{item.data.title}</a> <span class="small">— {item.data.date?.toISOString().slice(0,10)||"undated"} · {item.data.type}</span></li>)}</ol><h2>Legacy source</h2><p>The exact former Jekyll implementation is preserved in the site repository on <code>legacy-jekyll</code>. Old public post URLs redirect here or to a reviewed successor page.</p><p><a href="https://github.com/skcKenneth/skcKenneth.github.io/tree/legacy-jekyll/_posts">Browse legacy post source on GitHub</a>.</p></article></div></BaseLayout>
